               <floruit notBefore="1847" notAfter="1900">He was a prince, royal councillor and provincial governor. He was the son of 
                  <persName ref="PRS8346sahlase">Śahla Śǝllāse</persName>, born and brought up at <placeName ref="LOC1465Ankoba">ʾAnkobar</placeName>. 
                  He emerged as a prominent military leader immediately after the death of his father, <persName ref="PRS8346sahlase">Śahla Śǝllāse</persName>. 
                   In<date>1847-49</date>,  he campaigned in <placeName ref="LOC5482Salale">Salāle</placeName> 
                  and the neigbouring districts of <persName ref="ETH1012Abbicu">ʾAbbičuu</persName>. 
                  A few years later, he was captured
                  by
                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"> 
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                     Tewodros II</persName> and 
                  was confined at <placeName ref="LOC4547Maqdal">Maqdalā</placeName>. After his release by the British in <date>1868</date>, he returned to 
                  <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> and submitted to 
                   
                  <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Mǝnilǝk II</persName> to whom he was loyal until his death. </floruit>
                  <death when="1900"/>
                  
               </person>
               
